column5: This looks like it's all Slate Falls Airways planes out of Sioux Lookout. It's who we used for years and years until we switched to a drive-in trip. Some cool footage though. If you have never done a fly-in, I highly recommend one.http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=1w2eexa2P6Yp.s. I was going to steal this and post as my own find..........but Hawkfan sent me the link. lol
Cool video. I really respect those pilots. Not enough to tip them though.Hey Hey! I was just kidding!Hooks

Thanks Sin and Hawkfan, today is one more day that the cabin fever is reduced. Cool video! Quote: Originally Posted by HeHooksHimselfCool video. I really respect those pilots. Not enough to tip them though. Hey Hey! I was just kidding! HooksYea, yea, yea, I hear ya now.

Ha, I clicked on the guys username and it turns out he commented on a video I did in 2008. He was OUR PILOT on our flight in 2008. The video quality isn't great and I know I've probably posted it before but here is some footage from our 2008 trip.And, we DO tip. http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=pLYYpbILr4c
Cool video,wish i didnt watch that thats 16 weeks away,cant wait,oh well there is ice fishing,great video
Here are your fly-in options at this time of the year.http://i1178.photobucket.com/albums/...ps39a5e703.jpg
It can be had for $199,000. Eager seller. Might take less. Maybe a lot less.
Connie, last I heard he had it listed for $225, cold weather special now I guess. It is beautiful plane, would look good in front of your garage.
My wife won't even let me have an F Farmall. Would look great in my front yard and I could use it for about 20 minutes every year to plow my 40' x 45' vegetable garden.
If you like bush planes, you must attend the Norseman festival in Red Lake in July.
